name: dflowfm
upstream: Deltares Delft3D / D-Flow FM (Delft3D Flexible Mesh Suite)
upstream-repo: https://github.com/Deltares/Delft3D (Delft3D-main snapshot)
branch: main
version: BMI_API_VERSION 1.0 (BMI_API_VERSION_MAJOR 1, BMI_API_VERSION_MINOR 0, include/bmi.h)
extracted-from: Delft3D-main/ (local checkout at repo root)
extracted-on: 2026-07-15
extracted-scope: src/engines_gpl/dimr/packages/dimr_lib/include/bmi.h ONLY
                 (BMI interface contract snapshot; no Fortran kernel, no engine source)
vendored-to: extern/dflowfm/include/bmi.h
license: Delft3D multi-license (Deltares-owned code AGPL/GPL/LGPL family; see
         third_party/licenses/dflowfm-LICENSE, verbatim copy of upstream LICENSE).
         Decided approach: contract-snapshot-only. The AGPL/GPL D-Flow FM kernel
         is NOT vendored, NOT statically linked, and NOT compiled into this repo;
         the engine is consumed only as a runtime-loaded shared library resolved
         by symbol name (libs/coupling/river DFlowFMEngine). Only the BMI header
         contract is copied for interface documentation and spike fallback use.
patches: none
build: not built. cmake main graph does not compile anything under extern/dflowfm/.
       spikes/dflowfm/CMakeLists.txt may use extern/dflowfm/include as a bmi.h
       find_path fallback when DFLOWFM_SOURCE_DIR does not provide it.
abi-boundary: bmi.h must not be included by any main-graph public header or DTO;
              DFlowFMEngine declares its own function-pointer typedefs and loads
              the DLL at runtime (project-layout-design.md firewall; IDFlowFMEngine
              wraps lifecycle and state read/write only).
